		<td><b>SNES emu with &quot;Force NTSC/PAL&quot;?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Without downloading all of them and blowing hours, does anyone know if there is one that has this option? I want to test if uCON64's region forcing works on a few PAL exclusive games I'm converting for myself.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>byuu</b> [ Sat Mar 01, 2014 10:54 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: SNES emu with &quot;Force NTSC/PAL&quot;?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You can force it in higan by editing the created game folder's manifest.bml and changing &quot;region=NTSC&quot; (first line of the file) to PAL, or vice versa.<br /><br />Most likely possible with the other emulators, too.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
